    {
      "id": 258835,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "@ronnyx2017 discovered an issue that prevented MetaMask from presenting informational UI elements regarding the message the user was signing. This occurred when interfacing with smart contracts compiled using `solc < 0.5.0` by removing two bytes from the call data. We would like to thank @ronnyx2017 for the detailed report, and bring this to our attention ultimately making MetaMask more secure.\n",
